<body class="d-flex flex-column min-vh-100">
 
    <main class="container flex-grow-1">
        <h1 class="mb-4">About D.E.W. Radio Station</h1>

        <div class="embed-responsive " style="width=300px; height=300px;">
            <iframe class="embed-responsive-item" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/PlqJBPw-M-8" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </div>
        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>D.E.W. Radio Station, founded by Richard  aims to inspire and lead communities through radio podcasts. We are registered as a Non-Profit Company (NPC) and can operate in various sectors beyond just broadcasting.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2>Our Mission</h2>
            <p>D.E.W. Radio Station aspires to be the broadcaster of choice, providing local content with a global reach, particularly covering the communities of Daveyton, Wattville, and Etwatwa.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2>Our Vision</h2>
            <p>We aim to inspire and lead community discussions through positive dialogue and quality content, allowing community members to express themselves and advance their dreams.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2>Objectives</h2>
            <p>Our primary objective is to be the voice of the local community, promoting ideas related to arts, culture, politics, education, and socio-economic matters, while fostering peace and harmony through dialogue.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2>Strategic Partnerships</h2>
            <p>D.E.W. aims to collaborate with community leaders, schools, police, businesses, and various associations to enhance its outreach and effectiveness.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2>Organizational Structure</h2>
            <p>We operate with about 50 volunteers, focusing on youth development. Our structure includes various managerial roles such as CEO, CFO, COO, and departmental managers.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2>Financial Goals</h2>
            <p>As a non-profit organization, we need funding to support our structure. We aim to raise R50,000 to establish a studio. Currently, we operate as a podcast but plan to evolve into a fully-fledged radio and TV service.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2>Our Team</h2>
            <p>Our team comprises skilled individuals experienced in broadcasting and administration, committed to delivering quality content promptly. We are governed by our registered members, who serve as the board and actively manage daily operations.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2>Target Audience</h2>
            <p>Our broadcast targets community development projects and individuals, including local leaders, professionals, and organizations in Daveyton, Wattville, and Etwatwa.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2>Business Values</h2>
            <p>D.E.W. Radio Station is committed to conducting its operations professionally, legally, efficiently, and transparently.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2>Podcast Model</h2>
            <p>We develop high-quality content, broadcasting through platforms like YouTube, Facebook, Instagram, and TikTok. Our team ensures interactive and professional content delivery, with broadcasts scheduled weekly.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2>Future Plans</h2>
            <p>While we currently operate as a podcast, we plan to acquire studio equipment and apply for a broadcasting license once restrictions are lifted. We aim to evolve into a fully-fledged radio and TV service.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-5">
            <h2>Get Involved</h2>
            <p>We're always looking for passionate individuals to join our team of volunteers. If you're interested in contributing to our mission, please get in touch with us!</p>
            <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Contact Us</a>
        </section>
